<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8431&amp;p=87994#p87994</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8431&amp;p=87994#p87994"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Graphic problem with Splatterhouse MMC3 Hack]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8431&amp;p=87994#p87994"><![CDATA[
Might as well put this out there. <br /><br />If you have a Game Genie, use this code. EZLVAZ<br /><br />It will fix the game. If it does try this.<br /><br />Or open the NES file in a hex editor. Goto 1E248 and change $C0 to $A0. Reburn PRG. Please don't sell cartridges.<br /><br />The problem for anyone that wants to know is back when I wrote the Splatterhouse MMC3 port/hack I forgot to initialize NameTable Mirroring. This wasn't noticed until later on because the initial cartridge and the PowerPAK all had power on values for mirroring of Vertical Mirroring. However many other MMC3 revisions and date codes have Horizontal Mirroring on powerup.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Tue Dec 27, 2011 10:58 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
